    <p>
      <div class="label">Personal History</div>
      <div class="columns">
        In my teens I self-taught 3D animation, thinking that I'd rather enjoy a career as a computer artist. Thankfully, just before art college destroyed my life for the wrong muse, I realized my passion was for the technology, not the artistry. So I ripped my career in half: computer programming for the fortune, and music/art for the fame. Thus, the stuff featured on this site sits in the space bounded by these interests — software, music, art, and their mutant offspring. Granted, I have neither fame nor fortune, but if you only aim for Mars, you'll never get to <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Triangulum_Galaxy" target="_blank">M33</a>.
      </div>
